        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 4:02PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 400 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorm wind
gusts over Beaverhead and Madison Counties. Movement was to the east
northeast.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
West Yellowstone, Sheridan, Virginia City, Alder, Monida, Lakeview,
Yellowstone Village, Laurin, Targhee Pass, Cameron, Raynolds Pass,
Snowline, Red Rock Pass, and Monida Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
